details:
Case 207 is an imported case involving a 40 year-old female Singapore Citizen who had been in the United Kingdom from 6 March to 11 March. She is currently warded in an isolation room at NCID.

She reported onset of symptoms on 10 March while she was in the UK and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 13 March. She was referred to NCID on the same day. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 14 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, she mostly stayed at her home at Yishun Central.
